hope that you can check and see that I've done it&nbsp;
correctly. So I have to admit here that, you know,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:20:40.260 --> 00:20:46.140
I'm not that familiar with this entire world.&nbsp;
I'm sort of just making the initial forays into&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:20:46.140 --> 00:20:50.580
it myself, and I have to admit that I often get a&nbsp;
little bit confused making these calculations. We&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:20:50.580 --> 00:20:55.920
just have to where exactly are we, you know, and&nbsp;
what level are we, etc. So if I feel a little bit&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:20:55.920 --> 00:21:01.620
like perhaps an intelligent but primitive&nbsp;
person who has never been to school might&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:21:01.620 --> 00:21:06.960
feel when they're subjected to primary school&nbsp;
mathematics and they have to learn arithmetic&nbsp;&nbsp;

